<br>
Taurkon and Calamiel are very dear friends of Lizz and I, and of the Ridgerunner family, from back in their days as Scenites.  I shall always call them Bro and Sis, simply because they are, and always will be.  They are truly &quot;sweet hearts&quot; in every sense that a Norrathian friend can be.<br>
<br>
So, when Taurkon told me they were joining the Twist of Fate family,  I immediately made some assumptions.  To tell the truth, although I'd seen members of your family in my travels, I actually knew very little about TOF as a whole family.  The assumption I made was that, if Taurk and Cala had joined you, you must be a quality group of people.  The post I saw in Inny.com about how you and FOH handled Ragefire reinforced that for me.  And this Chardok raid proved to me that my assumptions were absolutely on the mark. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
There are many names I could mention from the Chardok raid, too many to name without making this a huge post.  I must mention Belarios specifically.  This raid was masterfully crafted and implemented, and this greybeard raidleader learned a number of lessons about Chardok in particular, and about raids in general by watching him work.  The rest of your family was serious enough to accomplish the tasks at hand, without ever losing sight of having FUN.  I also noticed the FOH members who were there with us, and I understand how you found kindred spirits in that family.  I spent many moments either being very impressed, or having a belly laugh for the entire raid.  It just can't get any better than that.<br>
<br>
Thank you for helping us get the opportunity to move Lizz, Mizwraith, and Bodar along in their quests to acquire their epics in Norrath.  I hope we accomplished what was needed for the members of your family while we were there. <br>
<br>
I feel confident in saying for my family that we hope you will consider the Ridgerunners your friends in Norrath.  Taurkon and I have often talked about planning joint family raids, as far back as the Scenite days.  I hope that we can occassionally do things like that together. <br>
I think it would be fun. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If you ever need extra forces, help, or anything in Norrath, please don't hesitate to send a tell to our family.<br>
<br>
Again, thank you for a very enjoyable day in Norrath, for friendship given freely, and for being neighbors in Norrath that I'll proudly call my friends.<br>
<br>
Gregar Mataennoo<br>
Ridgerunner<br>
